The paper deals with stochastic influence maximization problems in social networks, which is a topic that falls under the scope of social network analysis and machine learning. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a new class of problems and a delayed constraint generation algorithm, which involves optimization and algorithmic techniques, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. The paper also exploits submodularity, which is a concept in optimization and combinatorics, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with optimization problems in game theory, which falls under the scope of cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
